<item>
            <title>[HBASE-963] Fix the retries in HTable.flushCommit</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-963</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Many are seeing writes not getting into tables since &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-748&quot; title=&quot;Add an efficient way to batch update many rows&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-748&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-748&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; was committed. As I explained to Jonathan: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;jdcryans&amp;gt; jgray: but I&apos;m pretty sure that under high load a split took too long and the write didn&apos;t get through&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;jdcryans&amp;gt; jgray: That part has to be refactored to be used with other kind of batching&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;jdcryans&amp;gt; jgray: because the exponential backoff retry logic is in HCM but I had to get the retry out of it...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So this issue is about getting the retry logic out of HTable, hopefully merging it with the rest of HCM.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
