                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12643010" author="jdcryans" created="Mon, 27 Oct 2008 18:43:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch shows how I plan to do the refactoring. Without &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-880&quot; title=&quot;Improve the current client API by creating new container classes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-880&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-880&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, it&apos;s very ugly but it should fix the rows that are not getting committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12643015" author="stack" created="Mon, 27 Oct 2008 18:55:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch is fine  &amp;#8211; would suggest that before commit, change the close so it just notes exception rather than close it since on close, there is nothing much that can be done about and IOE.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12643658" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 29 Oct 2008 21:16:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated after &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-966&quot; title=&quot;HBASE-748 misses some writes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-966&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-966&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Passes PE, accounts for all rows when auto flush is enabled and when it&apos;s not.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12644128" author="streamy" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2008 22:04:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 no issues for 24 hours&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12644190" author="jdcryans" created="Fri, 31 Oct 2008 01:32:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk. Thanks for testing Jonathan!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
